</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0B5646E02CE152DCB7FCB05087FCF2" blockId="17.[213,425,835,859]" box="[213,425,835,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DCB7FCB05087FCF2" box="[213,425,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Material examined</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0B5646E02CE152DCB7FC995092FC4B" blockId="17.[213,1169,874,994]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">
Numerous females, males and juvenile specimens, from site D, 
<quantity id="EA4CFBA3E02CE152DFD5FC99552FFC2B" box="[951,1025,874,898]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" unit="m" value="12.3">12.3 m</quantity>
depth, 
<quantity id="EA4CFBA3E02CE152D83EFC9955BFFC2B" box="[1116,1169,874,898]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" unit="m" value="28.0">28 m</quantity>
from mouth of Conic Island Cave, NHM Reg. Nos 2005.2719–2748. One female specimen from site C, 
<quantity id="EA4CFBA3E02CE152DDBEFC59533FFC6B" box="[476,529,938,962]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
depth, 
<quantity id="EA4CFBA3E02CE152DE0EFC59538FFC6B" box="[620,673,938,962]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</quantity>
from mouth of Conic Island Cave, NHM Reg. No. 2005.2718.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0B5646E02CE152DCB7FBE85016FB9A" blockId="17.[213,312,1051,1075]" box="[213,312,1051,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DCB7FBE85016FB9A" box="[213,312,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D0B5646E02CE152DCB7FBB0554DFA70" blockId="17.[213,1169,1091,1497]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">
This species was collected from the anoxic sediments at the back of the cave. This species is the fourth phoxocephalid to be recorded from the South 
<collectingCountry id="55A316D6E02CE152DFC4FB9152C4FBD3" box="[934,1002,1122,1146]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">China</collectingCountry>
Sea, only three genera and three species having been reported previously (
<bibRefCitation id="49252BB7E02CE152DF0AFB7152DAFB33" author="Lowry JK" box="[872,1012,1154,1178]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" pagination="309 - 342" refId="ref11138" refString="Lowry JK. 2000. Taxonomic status of amphipod crustaceans in the South China Sea with a checklist of known species. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology Supplement No. 8: 309 - 342." type="book chapter" year="2000">Lowry 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="EAB42DC5E02CE152D86AFB705016FB12" authorityName="Hirayama" authorityYear="1987" class="Malacostraca" family="Phoxocephalidae" genus="Harpiniopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vadiculus">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152D86AFB705016FB12" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Harpiniopsis vadiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from closely related species by the characteristic P7 basis, setation of epimeres 1–3, and the bevelled coxa 4. A complete description and illustrations of this species can be found in 
<bibRefCitation id="49252BB7E02CE152DEA4FB1152A6FB53" author="Hirayama A" box="[710,904,1250,1274]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" pagination="1 - 62" refId="ref10643" refString="Hirayama A. 1987. Taxonomic studies on the shallow water gammaridean Amphipoda of West Kyushu, Japan. VII. Melitidae (Melita), Melphidippidae, Oedicerotidae, Phliantidae and Phoxocephalidae. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory 32: 1 - 62." type="journal article" year="1987">Hirayama (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="EAB42DC5E02CE152DFF7FB1155A7FB53" authorityName="Hirayama" authorityYear="1987" box="[917,1161,1250,1274]" class="Malacostraca" family="Phoxocephalidae" genus="Harpiniopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vadiculus">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DFF7FB1155A7FB53" box="[917,1161,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Harpiniopsis vadiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, along with the tanaidacean 
<taxonomicName id="EAB42DC5E02CE152DE68FAF152FAFAB3" authority="Bamber, 2000" authorityName="Bamber" authorityYear="2000" box="[522,980,1282,1306]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parapseudidae" genus="Pakistanapseudes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hodgsoni">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DE68FAF15201FAB3" box="[522,815,1282,1306]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Pakistanapseudes hodgsoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="49252BB7E02CE152DF55FAF152FAFAB3" author="Bamber RN" box="[823,980,1282,1306]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" pagination="39 - 52" refId="ref9795" refString="Bamber RN. 2000. Additions to the apseudomorph tanaidaceans (Crustacea: Peracarida) of Hong Kong. In: B Morton, editor. The marine flora and fauna of Hong Kong and southern China: Proceedings of the tenth international marine biological workshop; 6 - 26 April 1998; Hong Kong. Hong Kong: Hong Kong University Press. p. 39 - 52." type="book chapter" year="2000">Bamber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the anthuridean isopod 
<taxonomicName id="EAB42DC5E02CE152DD46FAD15352FA93" authority="Bamber 2008" authorityName="Bamber" authorityYear="2008" box="[292,636,1314,1338]" class="Malacostraca" family="Anthuridae" genus="Caenanthura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibex">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DD46FAD150CDFA93" box="[292,483,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Caenanthura ibex</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="49252BB7E02CE152DD8AFAD15352FA93" author="Bamber RN" box="[488,636,1314,1338]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" pagination="855 - 876" refId="ref9865" refString="Bamber RN. 2008. New species of anthurid and arcturid Isopod (Crustacea: Peracarida: Isopoda) from Hong Kong. Journal of Natural History, 42 (9 - 12): 855 - 876." type="journal article" year="2008">Bamber 2008</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and the bivalve 
<taxonomicName id="EAB42DC5E02CE152DF53FAD1556DFA93" authority="(Hinds 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Hinds" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[817,1091,1314,1338]" class="Bivalvia" family="Semelidae" genus="Theora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DF53FAD15280FA93" box="[817,942,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Theora lata</emphasis>
(Hinds 1843)
</taxonomicName>
, is part of an assemblage of species so far found only (in 
<collectingCountry id="55A316D6E02CE152DE84FAB15244FAF3" box="[742,874,1346,1370]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
waters) in the sediments of this cave. 
<taxonomicName id="EAB42DC5E02CE152DD26FA915317FAD3" authorityName="Hirayama" authorityYear="1987" box="[324,569,1378,1402]" class="Malacostraca" family="Phoxocephalidae" genus="Harpiniopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vadiculus">
<emphasis id="1FC08A54E02CE152DD26FA915317FAD3" box="[324,569,1378,1402]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Harpiniopsis vadiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from the Ariake Sea, 
<collectingCountry id="55A316D6E02CE152D82AFA9255A3FAD0" box="[1096,1165,1377,1401]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Japan</collectingCountry>
, which is the largest embayment on the west coast of Kyushu. The inner half of this sea is muddy (
<bibRefCitation id="49252BB7E02CE152DD51FA5250CAFA10" author="Hirayama A" box="[307,484,1441,1465]" pageId="17" pageNumber="841" pagination="75 - 150" refId="ref10531" refString="Hirayama A. 1983. Taxonomic studies on the shallow water gammaridean Amphipoda of West Kyushu, Japan. I. Acanthonotozomatidae, Ampeliscidae, Ampithoidae, Amphilochidae, Anamixidae, Argissidae, Atylidae, and Cologomastigidae. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory 28: 75 - 150." type="journal article" year="1983">Hirayama 1983</bibRefCitation>
), a similar habitat to that of the cave sediments. This record extends the distribution of the species from West Kyushu, 
<collectingCountry id="55A316D6E02CE152DF06FA325287FA70" box="[868,937,1473,1497]" name="Japan" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Japan</collectingCountry>
, to 
<collectingCountry id="55A316D6E02CE152DFB6FA325570FA70" box="[980,1118,1473,1497]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="17" pageNumber="841">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
